questionResults.questionText: Tell me about the Adidas GMR smart insole
questionResults.response:
The Adidas GMR smart insole is a product that Denys Honcharenko worked on during his time at EPAM Systems, from February 2020 to June 2020. As the Lead Software Engineer, Denys was part of the team that developed this innovative smart insole system in collaboration with Adidas, Google (Jacquard technology), and EA Sports.

The Adidas GMR smart insole tracks real-world soccer performance and converts it into rewards in the EA SPORTS FIFA Mobile game. It features shot power measurement, distance and speed tracking, kick detection, FIFA Mobile integration, global leaderboards, and universal fit compatibility with any footwear.

Denys' work on this project involved bridging physical sports with mobile gaming, creating a unique experience for users. He also developed a BLE emulator that increased QA efficiency by 10 times, which was a significant technical innovation. The project was a success, with 7.4 million shots tracked and 215 million meters covered in the first few weeks.
